{
  "schema_name": "eywa_node_response",
  "schema_version": "v1",
  "orchestration_decision": "delegate",
  "decision_notes": "The problem asks for the minimum Hamming weight of the product 2023 * n. This is equivalent to finding the minimum number of ones in the binary representation of a multiple of 2023. Since 2023 is odd, this is equivalent to finding the smallest k such that there exists an n where 2023 * n has k ones. This is related to the order of 2 in the multiplicative group modulo 2023 or finding a number of the form 2^a1 + 2^a2 + ... + 2^ak that is divisible by 2023.",
  "helpers": [
    {
      "label": "helper_1",
      "instructions": "Analyze the prime factorization of 2023. Determine if 2023 is coprime to 2. Check if 2023 has any specific properties modulo small powers of 2. Specifically, verify if 2023 can divide a number of the form 2^m - 1 for some m. If so, k(n) = 1 is impossible (since 2023 is not a power of 2), so test if k(n) = 1 is possible for any n. Note that 2023 * n = 2^m implies 2023 divides 2^m, which is impossible for odd 2023. Thus k(n) >= 2. Check if k(n) = 2 is possible by checking if there exist integers a and b such that 2^a + 2^b is a multiple of 2023. This is equivalent to checking if 2^(a-b) is congruent to -1 modulo 2023 (if we assume a > b) or if 2^x is congruent to -1 mod 2023 for some x."
    },
    {
      "label": "helper_2",
      "instructions": "Investigate the existence of k(n) = 2. A value of k(n) = 2 exists if and only if there exists an integer x such that 2^x is congruent to -1 modulo 2023, or more generally, if there exist a, b such that 2^a + 2^b = 2023 * n. This is equivalent to 2^b(2^(a-b) + 1) = 2023 * n. Since 2023 is odd, we need 2^x + 1 to be a multiple of 2023 for some x. Test this by checking the order of 2 modulo the prime factors of 2023. The prime factorization of 2023 is 7 * 17^2. Check if there is an x such that 2^x = -1 mod 7 and 2^x = -1 mod 289. If such an x exists, k(n) = 2. If not, test if k(n) = 3 is possible by checking if 2^a + 2^b + 2^c is a multiple of 2023."
    }
  ],
  "synthesis_brief": "Combine the results to determine the minimum k. First, confirm k(n) cannot be 1. Second, use the results from the modular arithmetic checks to see if 2^x = -1

